    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nIf the first showing of a buffer is done inside floating window with `style = 'minimal'`, then later showing this same buffer in normal window will use those \"minimal\" window-local options (like no number column, for example).\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create config file:\r\n```lua\r\n-- Initialize buffers\r\nlocal buf_id_1 = vim.api.nvim_create_buf(true, false)\r\nlocal buf_id_2 = vim.api.nvim_create_buf(true, false)\r\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(buf_id_1, 0, -1, false, { 'This is buffer 1' })\r\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(buf_id_2, 0, -1, false, { 'This is buffer 2' })\r\n\r\n-- Show first buffer in normal window with number column\r\nvim.wo.number = true\r\nvim.api.nvim_win_set_buf(0, buf_id_1)\r\n\r\n-- Show second buffer in floating window without number column\r\nlocal float_opts = { relative = 'editor', row = 1, col = 1, width = 10, height = 10, style = 'minimal' }\r\nlocal float_win_id = vim.api.nvim_open_win(buf_id_2, false, float_opts)\r\nvim.api.nvim_win_close(float_win_id, true)\r\n```\r\n2. Execute `nvim -u <path-to-config-file>`. This should show first buffer with number column.\r\n3. Type `:bnext`. This will show second buffer and will remove number column. Going back and forth between first and second buffers will consistently apply their first window-local options.\r\n\r\n**Note**: This doesn't depend on whether the buffer is the one with which floating window is initialized. The following third paragraph with creating floating window still produces the same behavior:\r\n```lua\r\nlocal float_opts = { relative = 'editor', row = 1, col = 1, width = 10, height = 10, style = 'minimal' }\r\nlocal float_win_id = vim.api.nvim_open_win(buf_id_1, false, float_opts)\r\nvim.api.nvim_win_set_buf(float_win_id, buf_id_2)\r\nvim.api.nvim_win_close(float_win_id, true)\r\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nExecuting `:bnext` show the second buffer without affecting current window-local options.\r\n\r\nThe following modifications of config file work as expected:\r\n- Completely removing paragraph with showing floating window.\r\n- First showing second buffer in normal window. So modifying second paragraph like this:\r\n```lua\r\nvim.wo.number = true\r\nvim.api.nvim_win_set_buf(0, buf_id_2)\r\nvim.api.nvim_win_set_buf(0, buf_id_1)\r\n```\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-1011+g7bf0963d4\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo, doesn't have Neovim's floating windows\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavourOS Linux x86_64 (6.4.12-arch1-1)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nst-0.9\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nst-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage",
